From 822bba6204e518d37c09b6a06cc9703db8129401 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shung-Hsi Yu <shung-hsi.yu@suse.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 13:30:43 +0800
Subject: [PATCH bpf-next 1/1] selftests/bpf: skip
 map_kptr/reject_scalar_store_to_kptr in cpuv4

The rejection message expected by map_kptr/reject_scalar_store_to_kptr is
specific to BPF_STX, thus on test_progs-cpuv4, the test will fail due to the
use of BPF_ST instruction that is only available in v4 instruction set:

  ...
  6: (15) if r0 == 0x0 goto pc+1        ; R0=map_value(map=array_map,ks=4,vs=32)
  ; *(volatile u64 *)&v->unref_ptr = 0xBADC0DE; @ map_kptr_fail.c:399
  7: (7a) *(u64 *)(r0 +8) = 195936478
  BPF_ST imm must be 0 when storing to kptr at off=8
  processed 7 insns (limit 1000000) max_states_per_insn 0 total_states 0 peak_states 0 mark_read 0
  =============
  EXPECTED   SUBSTR: 'invalid kptr access, R'
  #214/20  map_kptr/reject_scalar_store_to_kptr:FAIL

There does not seem to be an easy way to have different expected message for
different cpu flavor. And CAN_USE_BPF_ST merely detects whether the compiler
supports BPF_ST instruction, but not whether such instruction will be emitted,
so workaround the failure by guard the execpted message with CAN_USE_BPF_ST
macro.

Signed-off-by: Shung-Hsi Yu <shung-hsi.yu@suse.com>
---
 tools/testing/selftests/bpf/progs/map_kptr_fail.c | 6 +++++-
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/progs/map_kptr_fail.c b/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/progs/map_kptr_fail.c
index f11848dfa78f..03f260b1e823 100644
--- a/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/progs/map_kptr_fail.c
+++ b/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/progs/map_kptr_fail.c
@@ -386,7 +386,11 @@ int kptr_xchg_possibly_null(struct __sk_buff *ctx)
 }
 
 SEC("?tc")
-__failure __msg("invalid kptr access, R")
+__failure
+#ifndef CAN_USE_BPF_ST
+/* BPF_STX-specific error message */
+__msg("invalid kptr access, R")
+#endif
 int reject_scalar_store_to_kptr(struct __sk_buff *ctx)
 {
 	struct map_value *v;
-- 
2.54.0

